      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition and translation is based on <ref target="bibl:MNOVH2014">Nakanishi and von Hinüber 2014</ref>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" rend="break-none" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  <app><lem source="#MNOVH2014">siddhaṃ ||</lem><rdg source="#Poonacha2013">sidhaṃ</rdg></app> raño 
	  <persName key="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi">gotamīputasa
	  siriyaña <app><lem source="#MNOVH2014">sātakaṇ<unclear>i</unclear>sa</lem><rdg source="#Poonacha2013">sātakanisa</rdg></app></persName>
	  <date when-custom="11" datingPoint="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi" datingMethod="cal:regnal">sa<unclear>va</unclear> 10 1</date>
	  <lb n="2"/>
	  hematāna <app><lem source="#MNOVH2014">pakhe</lem><rdg source="#Poonacha2013">pakha</rdg></app> 1 diva 1 bhikhusa
	  dhamakadhikasa <persName key="pers:Kan-Bodhika">bodhikayasa</persName>
	  <lb n="3"/>
	  chata deyadhama sahā mātāpitūhi sahā ca bhātū<app><lem source="#MNOVH2014">bhaginihi</lem><rdg source="#Poonacha2013">bhaginīhi</rdg></app>
	  <lb n="4"/>
	  savalokahitāya
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  Success! In the year 11 of King 
	  <persName key="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi">Gautamīputra
	  Śrīyajña Sātakarṇi</persName>, in the 1st half-month
	  of the winter, on the 1st day. The pious gift of the
	  monk (and) preacher
	  <persName key="pers:Kan-Bodhika">Bodhika</persName>,
	  together with (his) parents and with (his) brothers and sisters
	  for the well-being of the whole world.
	</p>
      </div>
